**Convert Markdown to HTML**

To convert Markdown text to HTML, you can use the following function:

### `markdown_to_html` **(C++ Function)**
### **Input**: 
- `markdown_text`: A reference to a `std::string` containing the Markdown-formatted text.

### **Output**: 
- `html_text`: A `std::string` containing the converted HTML-formatted text.

### Implementation:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <string>

// Function to convert Markdown to HTML
std::string markdown_to_html(const std::string& markdown_text) {
    // Initialize the HTML string
    std::string html_text;

    // Add the opening HTML tag
    html_text += "<p>";

    // Loop through each character in the Markdown text
    for (char c : markdown_text) {
        // Check if the character is a newline
        if (c == '\n') {
            // Add a line break in the HTML text
            html_text += "<br>";
        } else {
            // Add the character to the HTML text
            html_text += c;
        }
    }

    // Add the closing HTML tag
    html_text += "</p>";

    return html_text;
}
```

